title: Cruise ship passenger reported missing in Seattle
text: Travel Links Yesterday's Places SEATTLE (AP) -- Holland America says a passenger is missing after its Alaska cruise ship Statendam docked in Seattle. The company said in a written statement the 64-year-old man was aboard the vessel when it sailed from Victoria, British Columbia, Sunday night, but did not check off the ship as expected after it docked in Seattle on Monday morning. Holland America said that per maritime law it notified the U.S. and Canadian Coast Guards as well as the FBI and was searching the ship for the passenger, described as a U.S. citizen who was traveling alone. The Statendam had sailed a 14-day roundtrip cruise from Seattle to Alaska.
